My cousin actually recommended this location. Said it was better than Harold's 👀. Tried it the first time & it wasn't hitting. We ordered 10 wings & 10 fish. It was okay but the fish was heavy(type of grease) so I didn't eat it.They did skimp us on the fries & put mild sauce on top when we asked for it to be on the side. BUT I decided to give it another try and called my order in. Ordered a 6 piece wing. Waited less than 5 min for it when I got there. My food was fresh. I had an ample amount of fries that I was even able to share and the chicken was great! Now a few things to keep in mind. This place is in the hood. The staff can and may have attitudes depending on the day or how you come at them and yes they are behind bullet proof glass for their protection. A plus is that you can see your food being prepared and it's cheap. I definitely advise eating it as soon as you get it. Certain foods just taste better fresh and not warm or reheated.
